physical_appearance: This is an image of sandy beach filled with tall palm trees that reach to the sky. Stuck into the sand are rows of chopped  tree trunks. The print is framed in a black-and-white frame. Yellowing has occurred along the edges of the print.
sgcool_label_text: Ho Koon Sang was a member of the Photographic Society of Singapore and an Associate of the Royal Photographic Society in London. This photograph was part of a set of 12 prints sent to the Royal Photographic Society in 1956.
